============================================================
PART 3: Is c3(v) constant for regular tournaments?
============================================================
  n=7: c3=14, 3c3/n = 6.0
  (n^2-1)/8 = 6.0
  c3(v) = 6 for ALL regular n=7 tournaments (100 samples)
  This is a well-known result: in regular tournaments, every vertex
  is in the same number of 3-cycles = (n^2-1)/8

============================================================
PART 4: Expressing K algebraically
============================================================

  For n=7: L = c3(v) = 6, c3 = 14
  K = c5 + butterfly - n*L*(L-1) - 3*c3
  K = c5 + butterfly + (-252)
  K_expected = -126
  So: c5 + butterfly = 126

  Verification:
    c5=36, butterfly=90, c5+butterfly=126, K_formula=-126, K_actual=-126, OK
